      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "ASSIGNING VALUES TO KEYS"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "When a key assignment table is displayed, the name of the key"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "is listed on the left and the assigned key contents are listed"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "on the right.  For example, the CTRL key assignments:"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "NAME             VALUE"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Ctrl A+          x'01'"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Ctrl B+          x'02'"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Ctrl C+          x'03'"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "The name information is a non-modifyable label applied to the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "associated key.  In this case, it represents the key combinations"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "of holding down the \"Ctrl\" key and pressing 'A', 'B', or 'C'."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "SPF/PC translates the typed key into the value displayed on the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "right.  In the above example, \"Ctrl-A\" gets mapped to the data"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "character Hex-01."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "field_row",
        "fields": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "(Press"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "ENTER+to continue)"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
